Hello and welcome back to The Best & The Brightest. I=E2=80=99m Leigh Ann
Caldwell, back at my computer after Washington=E2=80=99s favorite St. Patri=
ck=E2=80=99s Day tradition: the annual lunch on Capitol Hill where everyone=
 tells stories about how Irish they are. This year, Speaker Mike Johnson ho=
sted President Trump and Irish Taoiseach Miche=C3=A1l Martin. Sl=C3=A1inte!

=C2=A0

Separately, I sat down for tea with Kevin
Sherry, the C.E.O. of Enterprise Ireland, a company that helps Irish busine=
sses start, scale, and grow globally. Sherry and his team are making the ro=
unds along with loads of Irish officials who are in town to tout Irish inve=
stment in the U.S.=E2=80=94and who, like the rest of the world, are nervous=
